 Port Elizabeth - The Nelson Mandela Bay Municipality on Thursday advised residents and businesses that the R75 Uitenhage Road, near Joe Slovo, and the M19 Perseverance Road that were closed due to protest action in the morning have since been re-opened. "The situation is now calm," the municiplity said. "A joint team by South African Police Services and the Metro Police continues to monitor all the affected areas." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One.   